    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "I have seen such reports in the past, and I'm not very sure if this is actually the case. Since we are using shared pointers throughout the codebase, the only thing I could think of that could cause this would be circular references.\r\n\r\nIn any case, since the amount leaked is not too big and the compiler is not a long-running process anyway, I would prioritize this rather low.",
